sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>SA Token Auth
    participant DNS as ClusterDNS<br/>53/UDP
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>PyTorch:23456/TCP
    participant Worker as Worker Pod<br/>PyTorch:23456/TCP
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>UWM
    participant Volcano as Volcano Scheduler

    Note over User,Volcano: Flow 1: Training Job Creation

    User->>K8sAPI: Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>User credentials
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch notification<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create headless services<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Services created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create training pods<br/>master-0, worker-0, worker-1
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Pods created

    Note over User,Volcano: Flow 2: Gang Scheduling (Optional)

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup<br/>scheduling.volcano.sh
    K8sAPI-->>Volcano: PodGroup created
    Volcano->>K8sAPI: Schedule all pods atomically<br/>All-or-nothing

    Note over User,Volcano: Flow 3: Distributed Training Communication

    Master->>DNS: Resolve worker-0.service<br/>DNS query
    DNS-->>Master: Pod IP address
    Master->>Worker: Training coordination<br/>23456/TCP plaintext
    Worker-->>Master: Gradient updates<br/>23456/TCP
    Master->>DNS: Resolve worker-1.service
    DNS-->>Master: Pod IP address
    Master->>Worker: Training coordination<br/>23456/TCP

    Note over User,Volcano: Flow 4: Metrics Collection

    Prom->>Operator: Scrape /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Operator-->>Prom: Controller metrics<br/>reconciliation latency, job counts

    Note over User,Volcano: Flow 5: Job Completion

    Master->>K8sAPI: Update job status<br/>Succeeded
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch notification
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>Conditions: Complete
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job completed
